Document: PacketPeerExtension
Path: godot/classes/class_packetpeerextension.rst
Summary: Virtual methods for handling packet data in PacketPeerExtension, including retrieving packet counts, sizes, and transferring data buffers.

Method: _get_available_packet_count() → int. Virtual, required, const method. Returns the number of available packets.

Method: _get_max_packet_size() → int. Virtual, required, const method. Returns the maximum size of a single packet.

Method: _get_packet(r_buffer: const uint8_t**, r_buffer_size: int32_t*) → Error. Virtual method. Retrieves a packet from the buffer, writing the data pointer and size to the provided parameters. Returns OK on success, ERR_* on failure.

Method: _put_packet(p_buffer: const uint8_t*, p_buffer_size: int) → Error. Virtual method. Sends a packet with the provided buffer data and size. Returns OK on success, ERR_* on failure.
